[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/ProjectExport/ProjectExportIntegrationTests.cs:30 por @Copilot]: `CustomTestCleanupAsync` calls `await base.CustomTestCleanupAsync()` first, but the integration test conventions require calling the base cleanup last so framework cleanup runs after any custom side-effect cleanup. Move the base call to the end of the method (after removing created requests and releasing scratch FileShare directories).
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/PDF/AnnotationExporterTests.cs:119 por @Copilot]: The `ResourceManager` in this test is created with a `DownloadRequestBase` that doesn't set `AsBuilt`/`AsBuiltIncludeFiles`. In production `ResourceFile.ResolveAsync` is invoked from `ResolveResourcesAsync` only for `request.AsBuilt` requests, and `FilesSubFolder`/zip-path setup is initialized only in that mode. Setting `AsBuilt = true` (and enabling the relevant include flags) or using the existing `GetResourceManager(...)` helper would make the test exercise the same configuration and avoid `FileZipPath` becoming null when the DMS folder is the root folder (no `\` in the returned path).

